						               													<description>SphereWars is a fantasy skirmish game based around player built warbands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using the I Go, You Go format-- the game requires miniatures, a ruler, and six sided dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combat, however, is fought simultaneously. An opposing roll will determine which unit bypasses the defense of the other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Magic is also done simultaneously&amp;mdash;with one side attempting to counter the magic of the other. Using &amp;ldquo;power gems&amp;rdquo;, players attempt to bluff each other into over spending their gems and leaving them vulnerable for the next spell.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every warband must have a leader figure, but that leader can only command figures within 5&amp;quot;. Courier figures are required to deliver orders to any units outside of that range. Orders range from bonuses to automatically passing morale checks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Currently there are four factions are available: The Alliance (aka The Legion of the One Hundred Hearts), The Soimi, The Herd's of Urueh and the Adepts of Malesur.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On September 2011 a new race is released:The Newborns, that will also bring powder, technology and war machines to combat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The miniatures for the game are 28mm in size, and they are  unassembled and unpainted.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Official Website: www.spherewars.com&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
